


Gdrain(2G)           GRASS Reference Manual            Gdrain(2G)



NAME
     Gdrain - Traces a flow through an elevation model
     (G Language Tool)

SYNOPSIS
     Gdrain  output input E,N [E,N] ...

     Gdrain  output input

     Gdrain  output=mapname input=mapname coor=E,N [coor=E,N] ...

DESCRIPTION
     Gdrain traces a flow through a lowest cost path in an
     elevation model.  The elevation surface might be the
     cumulative cost map generated by the Gcost tool.  The output
     result will show one or more lowest-cost paths between each
     user-provided location and the low spot in the model.
     Consider the following example:

     Input:                            Output:
        ELEVATION SURFACE                 LEAST COST PATH
      . . ----- . . . . . . . . . .      . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
      . 20| 19| 17. 16. 17. 16. 16.      .   . 1 . 1 . 1 .   .   .   .
      . . |___| . . . . . . . . . .      . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
      . 18. 18. 24. 18. 15. 12. 11.      .   .   .   .   . 1 .   .   .
      . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .      . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
      . 22. 16. 16. 18. 10. 10. 10.      .   .   .   .   . 1 .   .   .
      . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .      . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
      . 17. 15. 15. 15. 10. 8 . 8 .      .   .   .   .   .   . 1 .   .
      . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .      . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
      . 24. 16. 8 . 7 . 8 . 0 .12 .      .   .   .   .   .   . 1 .   .
      . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .      . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
      . 17. 9 . 8 . 7 . 8 . 6 .12 .      .   .   .   .   .   .   .   .
      . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .      . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .

     The user-provided starting location in the above example is
     the boxed 19 in the left-hand map.   The path in the output
     shows the lowest cost corridor for moving from the starting
     box to the lowest possible point.  This is the path a
     raindrop would take in this landscape.

OPTIONS
     One or more points can be provided on the command line. The
     input options are as follows:

     input=mapname
          Name of cell map containing grid cell cost information.

     output=mapname
          Name of cell map to contain results.

     coor=E,N



GRASS 3.2                U.S. Army CERL                         1






Gdrain(2G)           GRASS Reference Manual            Gdrain(2G)



          These are the map E and N grid coordinates of a
          starting point.  This option can be repeated for as
          many points as desired.  (But, see BUGS below.)

BUGS
     Currently, Gdrain will not actually provide output for more
     than one pair of input coordinates stated on the command
     line.
     Gdrain also currently finds only the lowest point in the
     input file that can be reached through directly adjacent
     cells that are less than or equal in value to the cell
     reached immediately prior to it;  therefore, it will not
     necessarily reach the lowest point in the input file.  It
     currently finds pits in the data, rather than the lowest
     point present.
     Only one least-cost path is currently printed to the output
     file for the user.

SEE ALSO
     Gcost[2G]

AUTHOR
     Kewan Q. Khawaja, Intelligent Engineering Systems
     Laboratory, M.I.T.































